I. Scope
DNAcrypt-AI is provided for research use only and has not been validated for personal, clinical, diagnostic, enterprise, or production use. It is a composite software framework developed and maintained by Marvin De los Santos through ChordexBio or himself. DNAcrypt-AI incorporates proprietary components including, but not limited to:
- FAS2rDNA (a high-throughput DNA sequence reconstitution pipeline)
- Covary (sequence-informed machine learning model)
- Covary-encoder (a genetic encoding framework that structure DNA sequence into relational architecture) 

DNAcrypt-AI is solely offered for the purpose of generating, encrypting, decrypting passwords and/or cryptographic keys. Any use of DNAcrypt-AI, its proprietary and licensed components or its outputs outside this defined scope is not allowed, except to the extent expressly permitted by an applicable open-source or permissive third-party license governing a specific subcomponent or parts. Use of DNAcrypt-AI does not constitute a transfer, sublicense, or extension of rights to any underlying component, framework, or dependency beyond the explicit scope of DNAcrypt-AI.


