Permission is granted to international students, educators, and academic researchers (excluding Philippine-based users as defined in Section III) to use DNAcrypt-AI for non-profit and non-commercial academic or research purposes only, and only within the defined scope of DNAcrypt-AI.

The following are strictly prohibited without prior written permission or a separate license from the copyright holder:
- Commercial use of DNAcrypt-AI or its outputs
- Modification or creation of derivative works 
- Redistribution, sublicensing, or mirroring of the software
- Incorporation of DNAcrypt-AI into other software, pipelines, services, or platforms
- Extraction, reuse, adaptation, or repurposing of any embedded or underlying component (including FAS2rDNA, Covary, or Covary-encoder) for uses outside the scope and framework of DNAcrypt-AI

Use of DNAcrypt-AI does not grant users any rights or permission to use, modify, study, reverse-engineer, or deploy FAS2rDNA, Covary, Covary-encoder and related proprietary components for any purpose other than their execution or requirement as embedded within DNAcrypt-AI, except where a specific component, subcomponent, parts, or dependency is explicitly licensed under an open-source or permissive third-party license. All such components retain their original and independent licensing terms, which remain fully enforceable. Users are encourage to review and read the full licensing terms of these components.


III. Philippine-based users
A Philippine-based user is any user whose interests, affiliations, residency, or activities are connected to the Philippines materially, philosophically, or otherwise. All users considered Philippine-based users must obtain a valid license from the copyright holder prior to any use of DNAcrypt-AI, in any form such as research, education, commercial, testing, or otherwise. Philippine-based users include, but are not limited to the following:
1. Users physically located in the Philippines: Any user who is physically present in the Philippines while accessing or using DNAcrypt-AI, regardless of IP geolocation.
2. Users with Philippine-based affiliations or place of work: Users employed, enrolled, or officially affiliated with a Philippine institution, organization, or company, regardless of their current location.
3. Users whose organization is global but whose work location or designation is in the Philippines: Users working for international organizations but performing duties from a Philippine location or designated as Philippine-based.
4. International collaborations involving Philippine users: Any joint project, research, or sharing of DNAcrypt-AI that involves users, institutions, or facilities in the Philippines. All Philippine participants must hold a valid license, even if collaborators are outside the Philippines.
5. Philippine residents traveling abroad temporarily (without affiliations outside the Philippines): Residents of the Philippines using DNAcrypt-AI while temporarily outside the Philippines are still considered Philippine-based users and must hold a valid license to use DNAcrypt-AI.
6. Users within organizations owned by Philippine-based entities: Any user who is a member, employee, affiliate, or contractor of an organization (whether local or international) that is wholly or partially owned, managed, or controlled by a Philippine-based user.

Any user meeting the Philippine-based definition, requires a valid license, regardless of the user’s current location, organization, or circumstances.

